ral"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"horn (instrument used to signal others)","examples":[{"text":"وَنُفِخَ فِي الصُّورِ فَصَعِقَ مَنْ فِي السَّمَاوَاتِ وَمَنْ فِي الْأَرْضِ إِلَّا مَنْ شَاءَ اللّٰهُ ثُمَّ نُفِخَ فِيهِ أُخْرَى فَإِذَا هُمْ قِيَامٌ يَنْظُرُونَ","english":"And the trumpet is blown, and all who are in the heavens and all who are in the earth swoon away, save him whom Allah willeth. Then it is blown a second time, and behold them standing waiting!"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Tyre (a city in Lebanon)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"small palm-tree","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is plucked from the palm-tree sitting in the ground, the root of a palm-tree, a palm-trunk","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bank of a river, riverside","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side of the neck","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"forelock","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb from صُورَة (ṣūra, “form, image”).\n\nSeemingly a literary corruption of Hebrew שׁוֹפָּר (šōp̄ārā), hence doublet of شَبُّور (šabbūr).\n\nFrom Phoenician 𐤑𐤓 (ṣr /⁠ṣūr⁠/, “rock”).\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic צוּרָא (ṣūrā), variant of צַרְיָא (ṣaryā), צַארְא (ṣarā, “palm-band”), from Akkadian 𒍝𒊒𒌋 (ṣa-ru-ú /⁠ṣarû⁠/, “a part of the date-palm”).\n\nResultative to يَصُورُ (yaṣūru, “to bend towards a shape”)."},"ipa":["/sˤu.war/","/sˤuːr/","/sˤi.war/","/sˤawr/"]}